
Step 1: Locate interfaces with exactly one abstract method but without @FunctionalInterface.

Step 2: If the intended purpose is to be a functional interface, add the @FunctionalInterface annotation.

Step 3: If it is not intended to be a functional interface, the automated refactoring can either:

Skip the modification, or
Add @SuppressWarnings("PMD.ImplicitFunctionalInterface") (Note: In practice, it is recommended to only provide a warning rather than automatic modification.)
